            <fr:title text="About this book">About this book</fr:title>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>
This book is lots of bite-size subsections, organised together into sections, which are then organised into chapters.
It's intended to be read in order, together with <fr:link href="/0001/" title="Ellie Ripley" uri="https://www.my-great-forest.net/0001/" display-uri="0001" type="local">Ellie Ripley's</fr:link> logic class.
Along the way, there are exercises to help you practice the material as you learn it.
</html:p>
            <html:p>
At the end of the table of contents, you can also find "Reference" links.
These allow you to take a more direct and efficient view on the material: just the facts, definitions, and so on, without any of the discursive framing, metaphors, and intuitions that I try to convey in the main text.
These links can be handy if you're trying to look up an idea quickly!
</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
